  "texts": [
    "AI and more specifically deep learning models (e.g., GPTs) are helpful and commonly used in conducting literature reviews because of their programming to automatically identify key concepts and themes in the literature and to summarize large bodies of information (Watson et al., 2022).",
    "In addition to generating research questions and suggesting related research topics, deep learning models can be used to help with literature reviews in other ways (Mathew, 2023).",
    "Yet, what about the \"quality\" of work being generated through such models?",
    "There are several caveats and criticisms associated with using such models in theoretical discussions and literature reviews.",
    "For example, because they are based on statistical patterns in large amounts of data rather than on expert knowledge or critical analysis, they may not always provide accurate or reliable information (Grimmer et al., 2021)."
  ],
